              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " it starts to make sense to devise a \"better Common Lisp\". Which again never happened, and I'd be curious to know why exactly."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\nThe process of standardizing Common Lisp was so arduous was that the people who migrated in to it have forever been hostile to anybody and anything outside it. It's like, \"I just finally got all moved in. What do you mean you want me to move out? And you're trying to poach my neighbors?! Enemes FOREVA!\" Maybe I have the benefit of hindsight, but it doesn't make sense to gate something on a standard if it's going to be incompatible with it anyway."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
